description: Returns a list of Timestream for InfluxDB DB clusters.

nested_items.name: items
nested_items.description: A list of Timestream for InfluxDB cluster summaries.

nested_items.name: id
nested_items.description: Service-generated unique identifier of the DB cluster to retrieve.

nested_items.name: name
nested_items.description: Customer supplied name of the Timestream for InfluxDB cluster.

nested_items.name: arn
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: status
nested_items.description: The status of the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: endpoint
nested_items.description: The endpoint used to connect to the Timestream for InfluxDB cluster for write and read operations.

nested_items.name: readerEndpoint
nested_items.description: The endpoint used to connect to the Timestream for InfluxDB cluster for read-only operations.

nested_items.name: port
nested_items.description: The port number on which InfluxDB accepts connections.

nested_items.name: deploymentType
nested_items.description: Deployment type of the DB cluster.

nested_items.name: dbInstanceType
nested_items.description: The Timestream for InfluxDB DB instance type that InfluxDB runs on.

nested_items.name: networkType
nested_items.description: Specifies whether the network type of the Timestream for InfluxDB Cluster is IPv4, which can communicate over IPv4 protocol only, or DUAL, which can communicate over both IPv4 and IPv6 protocols.

nested_items.name: dbStorageType
nested_items.description: The Timestream for InfluxDB DB storage type that InfluxDB stores data on.

nested_items.name: allocatedStorage
nested_items.description: The amount of storage allocated for your DB storage type (in gibibytes).

nested_items.name: nextToken
nested_items.description: Token from a previous call of the operation. When this value is provided, the service returns results from where the previous response left off.
